parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, shut off, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off
loss of power
warning lights on the dashboard
inability to start the vehicle
and strange odors or burning smells.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduced engine power can cause the vehicle to slow down or lose acceleration, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The reduced engine power warning light illuminates
the vehicle slows down or loses acceleration
inability to maintain speed
and strange odors or burning smells.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall, shut off, or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
inability to remove the key
inability to start the vehicle
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or not shift properly, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or does not shift properly
warning lights on the dashboard
and strange odors or burning smells.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to not deploy in the event of an accident, leading to increased risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
and the airbags do not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear window defogger can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The rear window defogger does not work
and a burning smell is detected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to seize or become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the power steering fluid is leaking
the power steering warning light illuminates
and the vehicle is hard to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to seize or become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the steering column makes an abnormal noise
and the power steering warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to slip or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle is unable to move
and the traction control warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The traction control warning light illuminates
the engine reduces power
and the starting system is disabled.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Suspension and Tire Wear Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear of rear tires can lead to a loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Excessive wear on the inside edges of rear tires
uneven tire wear
vibration while driving
and loss of traction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Swaying or fishtailing while driving
uneven tire wear
vibration while driving
and difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
difficulty shifting gears
and loss of power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips when stopping at a light
the vehicle jerks or lunges forward when accelerating
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the vehicle shakes or rattles
the "Engine Hot/AC Off" message appears
and the speedometer fluctuates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical wiring harness can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gear shift button malfunctions
the shifter gets stuck in park
the key gets stuck in the ignition
the vehicle starts independently
and the vehicle rolls away without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Engine Overheat" warning light illuminates
the "Reduced Engine Power" message appears
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls
and the temperature gauge moves to the hot side.
